The paper discusses a new approach to managing IP addresses using blockchain technology, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the implementation of the system using smart contracts, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes conducting an experiment to test the system, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
